---
layout: post
title:  "Nonideal Effects on BJT"
date:   2019-11-02T14:25:52-05:00
author: Gyujun Jeong
categories: Research@HSNL
---

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The conditions of Ideal in BJT are constant doping, low level injection, width of emitter and base region are constant, energy gap is constant, and overall current is constant.
<br><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The collapse of these ideal conditions is called nonideal, and the effect in each nonideal situation will be examined.
<br><br>
There are six main nonideal effects:
<br><br>
1. Base Width Modulation ( = Early Effect)
2. High Level Injection
3. Emiter's Effective Bandgap Narrowing (Due to High-Doping)
4. Current Crowding Effect (Due to Resistance of Base)
5. Non-Uniform Base Doping Effect
6. Breakdown (Punch-through, Avalanche, Zener)
<br><br>
Now let's take a look at these six nonideal effects in a precautionary way.
<br><br>



